It also brings many negative effects , such as loss of face-to-face communicating skills , which are important in their workplace .
This essay will discuss the advantages and disadvantages of using social media in our daily life .
One of the significant advantages of using a popular social media site is that people can reach other easily , even if they have n't been in contact for a long time .
In this fast paced and competitive world , people may not able to keep in touch with others .
With the help of social media , people can able to upload their new discoveries and funny scenes and be kept up to date on new information from their friends .
Personally , I am studying overseas , and being busy studying keeps me away from contacting my old friends .
Using a common social media site with my friends helps me know their statuses nowadays .
And , I am able to easily find a common topic when I contact them .
In Singapore , many Malaysian cross the sea to work here .
Many of them are busy in work and are separated from their children .
One of Managers in my work place has the same situation .
After my Manager taught her mother how to use Facebook , she was able to upload video clips of her grandchild .
Therefore , my manager would not miss the moments of her daughter 's growth .
Social media sites are also a very useful tool for people to start a new friendship or relationship .
People get connected to others with similar preferences .
It is easier for people to approach others after knowing this information .
Students can exchange their experiences in a study even when they are in different countries .
People are able to share their culture , or pretty photos online ; therefore others can share the joy with them .
Thus , I believe that social media sites are one of the most useful tools to help people known each other better .
However , social media site is a double-edged sword ; it also brings in negative effects on our daily life .
One of the disadvantages that many people face is that they lose the interest in face-to-face communication .
Many people like to use language to pretend to be someone else , and lose confidence when they talk to each other .
