Social media sites suppose be a very useful and convenient tool to use and bring people get closer in this globalised world. Social media sites are a very useful and convenient means to bring people closer together in a globalized world .
The use of social media has largely influenced our ways in communicating with one another. The use of social media has greatly influenced our ways of communicating with one another .
People we communicate with online can become real life friends .
Social media has profoundly changed the way we exchange information and our interpersonal relationships .
There are both advantages and disadvantages as a result of this change .
Social media has reshaped the way we communicate with each other .
In real life , we communicate with one another as equal participants .
We share ideas , stories , and forge friendships based on mutual respect .
However , communication on social media is based in large part on " broadcasting and listening '' .
This occurs when we use Facebook to post pictures and statuses .
We are actively " presenting '' facades of our lives to others .
We tend to post pictures where we look our best and statuses that are funny .
We broadcast these facades of ourselves to others .
The images we choose to present are tentatively considered .
The audience is not some specific person , but everyone we might know , or even the entire world .
There is an element of seeking out for attention , rather than expressing one 's true opinion on social networks .
On the other hand , the viewers , are not the listeners .
They are just scrolling through lots of status pages and pictures to see if they think any of them are funny .
It is not the broadcasters themselves they care about , but their content .
This type of communication does not help when it comes to forging interpersonal relationships .
In real life , establishing friendships requires well-rounded understanding and caring for one another .
The latter requires face to face interaction so that our emotions are revealed to each other .
One can not truly understand a person by only stalking his/her facebook page where he/she has carefully choosen what to present .
One can not truly express their emotions to another by texting some = ) signs .
The broadcasting and viewing model is not good for forging relationships .
However , it is good for sharing information .
On social media , everyone is a broadcaster and a viewer .
With my social network account , I seldom read newspapers or go to news websites anymore because I can easily read them from the statuses of my friends .
If I am interested in politics , I can follow some politics newspapers or public figures .
I get news for sales , clothes , and cosmetics from my friends .
If some of my friends have horrible taste in clothes and he/she posts them often , I can simply block him/her off .
Information was circulated .
The most popular information is the most circulated , so I seldom miss it .
Social networks play a role in providing and filtering information .
This saves a lot of time I would otherwise spend reading newspapers or watching TV .
Personally , I feel more at ease on social media sites .
As you can see from the above points of view , I think social media can be used to forge more interest-based friendships .
With the help of social media , I become real life friends with those from online forums whom I share the same interest with .
By learning these common interests we find that we have many things to talk about .
The communication is then more focused on the content of the conversation .
This causes interpersonal skills to become less important , because our goal is not to impress others , but to get the information that we are both interested in .
In conclusion , I think the use of social media has reshaped interpersonal relationships from a more human-based friendship that requires sharing and caring between friends , to a more information-based friendship that requires a mutual interest .
There are advantages and disadvantages in itself , however , whether it is good or bad , we are still not sure .
It is just different .
Advantages and disadvantages of using social media in daily life
People living in the modern world really can not live without the social media sites , like Twitter and Facebook .
Almost all students and young adults have a Facebook or Twitter account .
It is true that social media makes it easier for people to connect conveniently .
However , it seems that , especially for some , sharing some parts of their lives , such as videos and photos on the social media sites really becomes necessary .
An extremely interesting and ironic phenomenon was discovered that a group of friends met and sat around one table , but none of them were really chatting with one another .
Instead , they were all more interested in posting pictures of this " cheerful '' meeting on their social media sites .
Therefore , there is need to discuss the advantages and disadvantages of social media .
Social media enables people from different parts of the world to communicate with one another .
People used to write letters and send postcards to keep in touch with those who lived far away .
It could take a few days or weeks for the recipient to receive the messages .
Nowadays , people can simply sit in front of the computer in their own rooms .
People on the other side will only need a second to receive the message .
Distance and time are no longer problems , which is convenient especially when instant contact is needed .
However , when people become more and more addicted to this convenience and fail to communicate with people who are close to them , their face-to-face interpersonal skills are lost .
Social media provides people with a way of talking and chatting that ca n't be considered real communication .
When one chats on media sites , there is no eye contact or emotional delivery , and the expressions must be typed in using a combination of punctuation marks .
For more convenience , sentences are shortened to three or four simple words such as " lol '' ( which means laughing out loud ) and " asap '' ( which means as soon as possible ) .
People go to great lengths to make their words as short as they can .
While they are communicating with people face-to-face , expressing themselves appropriately becomes a big problem .
Social media also provides people information about people and things that they are interested in .
For example , on Twitter it is exciting to follow people that you adore , like famous movie stars , business men and entrepreneurs .
It makes people feel extremely close to their admirers ' lives and works .
Almost every time , up-to-date news people care about can be easily obtained by refreshing social media sites on smart phones or laptops .
However , after you have registered on those unreliable social media sites , all the information you have filled in can be a weapon against you in the future .
Furthermore , not everyone on social media is honest .
The profile picture provided may not really be the person that user says he or she is .
That might just be because he or she wants to " decorate '' their face .
But there is the possibility that the person on the other side is deceiving you in order to obtain your information .
No pledge of authenticity risks people 's information that is shared on social media sites .
In summation , social media has advantages and disadvantages in people 's daily lives .
It shortens the distance between people from all over the world and makes instant communication possible .
It becomes more convenient to obtain and update information by using social media .
On the contrary , social media makes people lose their ability to communicate effectively in their real lives and makes people risk exposing their privacy to those whose identity can not be verified on the social media sites .
How does social media help change our lives ?
As the development of the technology has occurred , social media has become more and more significant in the world .
Everyone in the world uses it every day to express their feelings or ideas , which helps their friends know them better .
However , it also raises the concerns about whether or not it brings us more benefits or problems .
Although we can connect with friends wherever , it also reduces the chances for face to face conversations , which may affect our interpersonal skills .
Whether there are more pros than cons , becomes a tough question for everyone .
Many people enjoy and participate in social media since they have a closer view of their friends and what is going on in other places .
This is moreso to people out of the country .
To them , social media is the only way they can know everything that happened in their home country and they can show their lives to their loved ones as well .
These days , social media plays an important role in spreading information .
People can easily put their renting information on their Facebook account and wait for a response from others , which brings a huge amount of convenience .
It is quite significant , especially for those young teenagers , since they would rather go to these sites to see the news instead of reading the newspaper every day .
However , there are also a great number of people who oppose this technology .
They worry about the effect on teenagers who are still developing .
They pointed that actually , social media reduces the chance for us to talk to the people around us face to face .
The more time we spend on Facebook , the less time we will have to spend with our friends .
Today , it is quite common to be at party and see that people would prefer looking at their phones and reading all the posts on Facebook if they feel bored .
It makes people worry that if teenagers continue using social media frequently , they will decrease their ability to talk to people .
They feel it will become difficult for them to find any topics to communicate with other people about .
Personally , I strongly agree that social media brings more disadvantages , compared to advantages it gives us .
Although it is useful when we need to use it to let other people know we live a good life , it wastes a lot of time as well .
In another way , if we spend less time wandering on those sites , we may finish a book or do more meaningful things .
We should keep in mind that there are still ways for us to contact with our family or friends .
Everything will be bad if we do n't know how to use them wisely , no matter whether it is really good or not .
It is important for people to know to be cautious about the time spent on social media sites .
As stated above , I strongly believe that if we can use social media wisely rather than abusing it , we will all live a better life .
The advantages and disadvantages of social media
Nowadays , as technology is becoming increasingly advanced , more and more social media sites are showing up in daily life .
You can see people using Facebook or Twitter with their smart phones or ipads on buses or trains .
Some people say that these kinds of modern media may reduce the chance for people to communicate face to face .
This essay will discuss the pros and cons of using social media in modern society .
First of all , social media can make it more convenient for people to make friends and contact each other .
Years ago , before these modern products were available , people used phone calls , e-mails or letters to communicate with or contact those who lived far way .
these methods can be inefficient because it can take a long time to get a response .
However , social media solves these problems well .
People can contact their friends on the internet and get their replies very fast .
The communication is also not limited to words .
People can express themselves through pictures or emotions .
People can also get to know their friends ' state and mood by looking at their posts on line .
Moreover , people can be aware of what is going on in social situations , see the online comments , and share their own opinions on these websites .
These social media networks make people 's lives much more colorful and provide a lot of fun .
However , social media may do some harm to people 's lives .
It does make people spend more time on chatting on the Internet rather than communicating face-to-face , to the extent that interpersonal skills will be badly affected .
Some people spend a lot of time online and forget about their real life .
In my experience , I have met some people who can be very funny and interesting when chatting with them online .
However , they are quite boring when I talk to them in real life .
Teenagers are developing their interpersonal and social skills when they are growing up .
If they spend too much time on social media , it may interfere with the development of these skills .
They may feel uncomfortable when they communicate with people face to face .
Some may share less time with their family , and not know how to express themselves .
Moreover , some values shown on these websites are wrong and will affect teenagers by confusing them .
Some may even do something wrong .
In conclusion , the introduction of social media sites has been a double-edged sword .
It can make our life simpler .
People can promote their friendships and relationships through social media .
It can also make people forget to communicate to their family and friends in real life , which can negatively affect their interpersonal skills .
Overall , the advantages far outweigh its disadvantages .
We need to make the best use of social media and make it a fun way of adding some excitement when life is boring .
And try to bypass the shortcomings .
Remember to frequently send greetings to your friends and family .
It is easy to communicate wherever you are nowadays thanks to the advancement of technology .
Use of social media sites truly connects people .
People can know their friends ' recent looks and the interesting things that happen to people just by checking their Facebook or other social media sites .
It can not be denied that social media truly makes it easier for old friends to keep up with current information and gives them chances to communicate .
However , social media sites reduce face-to-face communication which affects interpersonal skills .
There are advantages and disadvantages of using social media in people 's daily lives .
First , the social media sites can connect people with their friends and parents .
People can express their emotions that they are too shy to express through text and pictures .
For example , on mother 's day , people are too shy to say " I love you '' to their mothers so they can type it on their mother 's facebook page .
Then their mother will understand their child 's emotion and feel warm .
On the other hand , when a teenager is studying in a foreign country , the internet is the only way that he can communicate with his parents and friends .
Therefore , social media is truly good for people .
Also , social media sites do n't only connect people closely to their friends .
People can also learn a lot of information about celebrities , such as President Obama and Bill Gates , on Twitter and Facebook , and study them first-hand .
They can learn how these people succeed , have the chance to talk to them and know these famous peoples thoughts by using social media .
On the other hand , people who need money to cure a disease or who are homeless can get the help they need quickly because people can share the information with people they know and spread the information around the world .
There are also problems with the population of social media .
When people rely on the social media to communicate with their friends and parents , they grow accustom to communicating by typing and not talking .
People even prefer to meet their friends online and gradually reject face-to-face communication .
Social media truly limits the interpersonal skills that people use to connect with friends .
Without true communication people lose the ability to see the difference between true and false .
There are many people on social media with a beautiful image and good content in their pages , however in real life , he or she may not have a job or live poorly .
Teenagers may believe these people and easily be cheated and lose money even their safety .
Social media is not safe which is bad for a teenager 's future development .
Overall , the appearance of social media helps many people in a lot of areas .
However , there are some disadvantages that will affect people to some degree .
Advantages and Disadvantages of Using Social Media in Our Daily life and Society .
Today , with the development of technology and society , social media has become more popular and even more important in our daily life .
We communicate with others using social media , such as Twitter , Facebook and microblogging more and more frequently .
There is no need for people to interact with others outside of there because they chat online , share pictures and funny stories .
People can build a relationship by social media but problems can come out .
People who do not how to interact personally , especially with strangers .
We need to talk about the pros and cons of social media in your daily life .
As for the pros , it is easier to know more about others and contact them .
One advantage is that it is more convenient to contact others by social media .
In the old days , if one wanted to tell important news to another , who lived far away , he need would need to write a letter and that is time consuming .
The long distances and time consuming methods of communicating , made spreading the messages very difficult at that time .
Because of that , people may not contact faraway friends and relatives unless there is something important .
However , now people can contact anyone all over the world who can use a computer at any time , and there is no delay of their messages .
Another advantage is that it is easier to know about others by social media .
If there was no social media , it would be difficult for people to know about strangers .
They may collect information about that person by asking friends , colleagues or family members .
The information collected may not be intact and true .
Unlike today , with the help with social media , people can easily get the information they want just by searching online , and know about what that person does each day .
As for the disadvantages of social media in our daily life , wasting time , causing illness related to sitting long time at the computer , quick-spread of rumor and fake news and , most importantly , making people lose the ability to talk to others face to face confidently .
It is weird that people sit around the table with their faces in their phones and do not talk with each other .
If there is a joke on their facebook page , they may talk to others saying , " hi , look , how ridiculous this is '' , then they laugh together .
Whether it is a party , dinner or just simply a get-together , there always are some people playing with their phones even their family and friends are in front of them .
In conclusion , there are both advantages and disadvantages of using social media in daily life .
People should enjoy the advantages of social media while being aware of the disadvantages and try their best to avoid those disadvantages .
Today 's world is considered to be the era of social media : sites like Facebook and Twitter , for example , are attractively connecting people around the world .
However , some people worry that social networks can affect interpersonal skills , as it reduces face-to-face human contact .
The advantages and disadvantages of using such social media in the society are as follows .
Nobody can deny social media 's advantages , as the benefit it provides in connecting people regardless of nationality , race , culture , and language .
Social media is a trending channel and a suitable mean of communication .
First , social media brings convenience to the world .
It has erased the boundaries of distance and time .
There are no more worries about the time it takes to deliver letters and packages .
Nowadays , thanks to the help of social media , you can contact your family and friends wherever you want with just one click .
You can share photos , videos , and all other meaningful experiences of your life .
More importantly , it is cheap and easy to use social media to do this .
Secondly , social media networks open the door of opportunity for people due to great benefits gained when connecting to others .
A lot of new graduates can find jobs thanks to Facebook and Twitter .
Young people can widen their relationships , meet new friends , and learn wonderful things about many parts of the world .
In the business area , social media is a good tool to use for developing and advertising products and services .
On the other hand , social media also has disadvantages , which have recently created worries in society and made it a controversial phenomenon .
More and more young people tend to live in the social media world a majority of their time and have reduced face-to-face human contact , which can affect interpersonal skills and relationships .
First and foremost , we should realize that the social media world is not always trustworthy and real .
Anyone can easily make up the personality and characteristics they want to portray .
They can be anyone .
Though social media do create relationships , relationships and friendships are only firm and real if people have gone through experiences and communicate through face-to-face interaction .
There is a story of a girl who lived in the social media world every night for eight years .
In a chat room , she created a close relationship with eight people .
She talked to them every night , trusted them and shared her life with them .
Eventually , she discovered that eight people became one as he was using eight different identities to chat with her .
Furthermore , the convenience of social media is also its weakness .
A lot of people use their true information on social media sites , which can lead to crimes and deception .
People can use the information to deceive family and friends to do bad things such as blackmail and theft .
Finally , social media does affect human interpersonal skills when people increase their time spent online , rejecting the chance to interact with others outside of the computer .
Recent research has shown that the more time people spend on social media sites , the less ambitious they become .
As a result , if the situation continues in this unexpected trend , the effects it will cause could be bad for the younger generation .
To put it in a nutshell , everything has its own pros and cons .
This is true of social media networks .
On one hand it is convenient and beneficial in connecting people and developing business , but on the other hand it can damage personal relationships and interpersonal skills .
Social media is only beneficial as long as we know how to use it in a correct and suitable way , with the combination of both social media sites and daily life interaction to develop people 's potential .
